The paper focuses on the problem of inverse reinforcement learning (IRL), which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence (AI) that deals with learning the underlying reward function of an expert given demonstrations. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. 

The paper also proposes a model-free density-based IRL algorithm and extends it to handle nonlinear IRL problems, which involves concepts from robotics (cs.RO), control systems (cs.SY), and computer vision (cs.CV). Therefore, these sub-categories are also likely.
